try_to_freeze() call!
> +	if (freezing(current)) {
Would it be possible to acquire the lock here instead, then recheck here?
Or use a per-thread lock?  (Yes, this would make the error checking path
have to acquire a very large number of threads, but...
							Thanx, Paul
